This directory is required to exist by examples/receiptctl/ggen.toml's
[templates].dir = "templates" config, but this example sources its actual
templates from its [[packs]] entries, not from local files here. Git does
not track empty directories, so on a fresh checkout (e.g. CI) this directory
was silently absent, causing `ggen sync run` to fail with FM-CONFIG-004
(templates dir unreadable). Same root cause as
examples/tcps-generated/templates/.gitkeep (see that file's note) --
discovered here via the justfile's guard-pack-proofs recipe, which syncs
this example too. This .gitkeep exists solely to keep the directory present
after `git clone`.
